## Files

- `src/hello_harness.sh` — Main script entry point.
- `tests/test_hello_harness.sh` — Shell-based tests (via bats or shunit2).

## Approach

- Single POSIX-compatible shell script.
- Parse flags with a simple `case` loop.
- Default name: "Harness".
- Print usage with a `usage()` function.

## Rejected alternatives

- **Python/Node script** — Introduces language dependency. Shell keeps the
  demo accessible to any project regardless of stack.
- **Inline in init.sh** — Would bloat the verification script. Keep
  hello_harness as a separate entry point.
